div.p: shared/middleware.RequireAuth one lifecycle per HTTP request
EXTRACT_HEADER r.Header.Get("Authorization") invariant: header value is raw string or ""
PARSE_BEARER strings.HasPrefix(v, "Bearer ") tokenStr = strings.TrimPrefix(v, "Bearer ") invariant: tokenStr non-empty
VERIFY_SIGNATURE jwt.Parse(tokenStr, keyFunc) keyFunc checks alg == HS256 HMAC-SHA256 vs JWT_SECRET invariant: alg is HS256; issuer == "url-shortener"
CHECK_EXPIRY claims["exp"] > time.Now().Unix() invariant: token not yet expired
INJECT_CLAIMS ctx = context.WithValue(r.Context(), ClaimsContextKey, claims) r = r.WithContext(ctx) invariant: claims.Sub, claims.Email non-empty
NEXT_HANDLER next.ServeHTTP(w, r) invariant: ClaimsContextKey present in ctx
REJECT 401 Unauthorized w.WriteHeader(401) body: {"error":"unauthorized"} Content-Type: application/json request terminates; next NOT called
ILLEGAL Skip VERIFY_SIGNATURE Security violation: unverified claims injected into context

Legend start/end state normal processing state success / data mutation state rejection terminal (401) happy-path transition rejection transition (labeled with HTTP status + body) ILLEGAL transition (must never occur)
